data.meta_description: Marge Piercy (born March 31, 1936) is an American poet, novelist, and social activist. She is the author of the New York Times bestseller Gone to Soldiers, a sweeping historical novel set during World War II.  “...I want to make with you  some bold new thing  to stand in the marketplace,  the statue of a goddess  laughing, armed and wearing  flowers and feathers...  ...I want  to force from this fierce sturdy  rampant love some useful thing.”
